	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">sleepy9090 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">i can't help you but out of curiosity what is it? are you making a standard eprom cart or flash cart or something?</div>
<br />
<br />I'm looking to make PCB's that I can use for Sega repro projects, but much more importantly for Sega Homebrew projects. Matt and I just produced Hangman SG which was coded from scratch by Adam Welch, and we're working with him on future (and substantially larger) projects. I know that a 4 MB board with battery backed SRAM will be perfect for literally ANY project that can be thrown at it, so I think that's the most logical to produce. I also hope that I can provide these for sale to members of the homebrew and repro communities to limit the number of "donors" used for projects. Because of this, I'm likely going to order 1,000+ boards.
<br />
<br />I'm not interested in purchasing actual boards from a member, just looking for a board schematic and board layout that I can personally send off to a manufacturer so that I can produce as many as I'd like. I'd certainly pay a decent price for that service, but I'm not looking to order a run of boards through a member.

		

		</td>
